{"word":"H352 - אַיִל - ʼayil - ah'-yil - Mighty","slug":"H352","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אַיִל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼayil"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ah'-yil"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Mighty"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>איל</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>'ayil</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>ah'-yil</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p><ol><li>ram<ol type='a'><li>ram (as food)</li><li>ram (as sacrifice)</li><li>ram (skin dyed red, for tabernacle)</li></ol><li>pillar, door post, jambs, pilaster</li><li>strong man, leader, chief</li><li>mighty tree, terebinth</li></ol> <p />Origin: from the same as <a href=\"#/H193\">H193</a> <p />TWOT entry: <a class=\"T\" href=\"S:0045 - 'wl\">45d</a>, e, f, g <p />Part(s) of speech: Noun Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H193\">H193</a>, <a href=\"#/H195\">H195</a>, <a href=\"#/H197\">H197</a>, <a href=\"#/H198\">H198</a>, <a href=\"#/H354\">H354</a>, <a href=\"#/H355\">H355</a>, <a href=\"#/H356\">H356</a>, <a href=\"#/H357\">H357</a>, <a href=\"#/H359\">H359</a>, <a href=\"#/H361\">H361</a>, <a href=\"#/H362\">H362</a>, <a href=\"#/H364\">H364</a>, <a href=\"#/H365\">H365</a>, <a href=\"#/H424\">H424</a>, <a href=\"#/H425\">H425</a>, <a href=\"#/H436\">H436</a>, <a href=\"#/H440\">H440</a>"}]}